{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"68ebbfc3-f305-4ff3-997a-f8dcd8ba02fe","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** (.NET 9), which supports modern patterns well. Here's the recommended approach:\n\n**Constructor injection** for `TestContext`, plus `[TestInitialize]` for both sync and async setup:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service = null!;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test initialization\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        var result = await _service.DoWorkAsync();\n        Assert.IsNotNull(result);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor injection** of `TestContext` is the modern MSTest 3.x approach (replaces the old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern).\n- `[TestInitialize]` can return `Task` for async init — no special attribute needed.\n- For **class-level** async setup, use `[ClassInitialize]` with `static async Task`.\n- Sync setup logic can go in the constructor itself or in a `[TestInitialize] public void Setup()` method.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0bc8a111-521a-4494-84b5-c71fd9ef5512","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use a constructor parameter or a `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property. In MSTest v3+, constructor injection is supported.\n\n2. **Sync initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` method.\n\n3. **Async initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with an `async Task` return type (supported in MSTest v2+).\n\nActually, let me be more precise about MSTest 3.x patterns:\n\n\n- `TestContext` can be injected via constructor, which is the cleanest approach in v3.8.2\n- Class-level setup uses `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]`, while per-test setup uses `[TestInitialize]` and `[TestCleanup]`\n- All of these support async by returning `Task`","outputTokens":645,"requestId":"981C:24244F:10319AF:1477176:69FFE118"},"id":"53204a0c-79b0-498a-ba41-654899faeb50","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:36:37.372Z","parentId":"5e5ba973-8286-48bc-ab14-da828cb22f2a"}
